65TEST(HasDescendant, MatchesDescendantTypes) {
66 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void f() { int i = 3; }",
67 decl(hasDescendant(loc(builtinType())))));
68 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void f() { int i = 3; }",
69 stmt(hasDescendant(builtinType()))));
70
71 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void f() { int i = 3; }",
72 stmt(hasDescendant(loc(builtinType())))));
73 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void f() { int i = 3; }",
74 stmt(hasDescendant(qualType(builtinType())))));
75
76 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("void f() { float f = 2.0f; }",
77 stmt(hasDescendant(isInteger()))));
78
79 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
80 "void f() { int a; float c; int d; int e; }",
81 functionDecl(forEachDescendant(
82 varDecl(hasDescendant(isInteger())).bind("x"))),
83 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 3)));
84}

86TEST(HasDescendant, MatchesDescendantsOfTypes) {
87 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void f() { int*** i; }",
88 qualType(hasDescendant(builtinType()))));
89 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void f() { int*** i; }",
90 qualType(hasDescendant(
91 pointerType(pointee(builtinType()))))));
92 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void f() { int*** i; }",
93 typeLoc(hasDescendant(loc(builtinType())))));
94
95 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
96 "void f() { int*** i; }",
97 qualType(asString("int ***"), forEachDescendant(pointerType().bind("x"))),
98 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Type>>("x", 2)));
99}

122TEST(StatementMatcher, Has) {

124 expr(hasType(pointsTo(recordDecl(hasName("X")))),
125 has(ignoringParenImpCasts(declRefExpr(to(varDecl(hasName("i")))))));

146TEST(TypeMatcher, MatchesClassType) {
147 TypeMatcher TypeA = hasDeclaration(recordDecl(hasName("A")));
148
149 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("class A { public: A *a; };", TypeA));
150 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("class A {};", TypeA));
151
152 TypeMatcher TypeDerivedFromA =
153 hasDeclaration(cxxRecordDecl(isDerivedFrom("A")));
154
155 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("class A {}; class B : public A { public: B *b; };",
156 TypeDerivedFromA));
157 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("class A {};", TypeA));
158
159 TypeMatcher TypeAHasClassB = hasDeclaration(
160 recordDecl(hasName("A"), has(recordDecl(hasName("B")))));
161
162 EXPECT_TRUE(
163 matches("class A { public: A *a; class B {}; };", TypeAHasClassB));
164
165 EXPECT_TRUE(matchesC("struct S {}; void f(void) { struct S s; }",
166 varDecl(hasType(namedDecl(hasName("S"))))));
167}

169TEST(TypeMatcher, MatchesDeclTypes) {
170 // TypedefType -> TypedefNameDecl
171 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("typedef int I; void f(I i);",
172 parmVarDecl(hasType(namedDecl(hasName("I"))))));
173 // ObjCObjectPointerType
174 EXPECT_TRUE(matchesObjC("@interface Foo @end void f(Foo *f);",
175 parmVarDecl(hasType(objcObjectPointerType()))));
176 // ObjCObjectPointerType -> ObjCInterfaceType -> ObjCInterfaceDecl
177 EXPECT_TRUE(matchesObjC(
178 "@interface Foo @end void f(Foo *f);",
179 parmVarDecl(hasType(pointsTo(objcInterfaceDecl(hasName("Foo")))))));
180 // TemplateTypeParmType
181 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("template <typename T> void f(T t);",
182 parmVarDecl(hasType(templateTypeParmType()))));
183 // TemplateTypeParmType -> TemplateTypeParmDecl
184 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("template <typename T> void f(T t);",
185 parmVarDecl(hasType(namedDecl(hasName("T"))))));
186 // InjectedClassNameType
187 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("template <typename T> struct S {"
188 " void f(S s);"
189 "};",
190 parmVarDecl(hasType(injectedClassNameType()))));
191 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("template <typename T> struct S {"
192 " void g(S<T> s);"
193 "};",
194 parmVarDecl(hasType(injectedClassNameType()))));
195 // InjectedClassNameType -> CXXRecordDecl
196 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("template <typename T> struct S {"
197 " void f(S s);"
198 "};",
199 parmVarDecl(hasType(namedDecl(hasName("S"))))));
200
201 static const char Using[] = "template <typename T>"
202 "struct Base {"
203 " typedef T Foo;"
204 "};"
205 ""
206 "template <typename T>"
207 "struct S : private Base<T> {"
208 " using typename Base<T>::Foo;"
209 " void f(Foo);"
210 "};";
211 // UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl
212 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(Using, unresolvedUsingTypenameDecl(hasName("Foo"))));
213 // UnresolvedUsingTypenameType -> UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl
214 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(Using, parmVarDecl(hasType(namedDecl(hasName("Foo"))))));
215}

285TEST(HasUnderlyingDecl, Matches) {
286 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("namespace N { template <class T> void f(T t); }"
287 "template <class T> void g() { using N::f; f(T()); }",
288 unresolvedLookupExpr(hasAnyDeclaration(
289 namedDecl(hasUnderlyingDecl(hasName("::N::f")))))));
290 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(
291 "namespace N { template <class T> void f(T t); }"

294 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(
295 "namespace N { template <class T> void f(T t); }"
296 "template <class T> void g() { using N::f; f(T()); }",
297 unresolvedLookupExpr(hasAnyDeclaration(namedDecl(hasName("::N::f"))))));

404TEST(Matcher, AnyArgument) {
405 auto HasArgumentY = hasAnyArgument(
406 ignoringParenImpCasts(declRefExpr(to(varDecl(hasName("y"))))));
407 StatementMatcher CallArgumentY = callExpr(HasArgumentY);
408 StatementMatcher CtorArgumentY = cxxConstructExpr(HasArgumentY);
409 StatementMatcher UnresolvedCtorArgumentY =
410 cxxUnresolvedConstructExpr(HasArgumentY);
411 StatementMatcher ObjCCallArgumentY = objcMessageExpr(HasArgumentY);
412 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void x(int, int) { int y; x(1, y); }", CallArgumentY));
413 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void x(int, int) { int y; x(y, 42); }", CallArgumentY));
414 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("struct Y { Y(int, int); };"
415 "void x() { int y; (void)Y(1, y); }",
416 CtorArgumentY));
417 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("struct Y { Y(int, int); };"
418 "void x() { int y; (void)Y(y, 42); }",
419 CtorArgumentY));
420 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("template <class Y> void x() { int y; (void)Y(1, y); }",
421 UnresolvedCtorArgumentY));
422 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("template <class Y> void x() { int y; (void)Y(y, 42); }",
423 UnresolvedCtorArgumentY));
424 EXPECT_TRUE(matchesObjC("@interface I -(void)f:(int) y; @end "
425 "void x(I* i) { int y; [i f:y]; }",
426 ObjCCallArgumentY));
427 EXPECT_FALSE(matchesObjC("@interface I -(void)f:(int) z; @end "
428 "void x(I* i) { int z; [i f:z]; }",
429 ObjCCallArgumentY));
430 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("void x(int, int) { x(1, 2); }", CallArgumentY));
431 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("struct Y { Y(int, int); };"
432 "void x() { int y; (void)Y(1, 2); }",
433 CtorArgumentY));
434 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("template <class Y>"
435 "void x() { int y; (void)Y(1, 2); }",
436 UnresolvedCtorArgumentY));
437
438 StatementMatcher ImplicitCastedArgument = callExpr(
439 hasAnyArgument(implicitCastExpr()));
440 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("void x(long) { int y; x(y); }", ImplicitCastedArgument));
441}

526TEST(MatcherCXXMemberCallExpr, On) {
527 auto Snippet1 = R"cc(
528 struct Y {
529 void m();
530 };
531 void z(Y y) { y.m(); }
532 )cc";
533 auto Snippet2 = R"cc(
534 struct Y {
535 void m();
536 };
537 struct X : public Y {};
538 void z(X x) { x.m(); }
539 )cc";
540 auto MatchesY = cxxMemberCallExpr(on(hasType(cxxRecordDecl(hasName("Y")))));
541 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(Snippet1, MatchesY));
542 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(Snippet2, MatchesY));
543
544 auto MatchesX = cxxMemberCallExpr(on(hasType(cxxRecordDecl(hasName("X")))));
545 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(Snippet2, MatchesX));
546
547 // Parens are ignored.
548 auto Snippet3 = R"cc(
549 struct Y {
550 void m();
551 };
552 Y g();
553 void z(Y y) { (g()).m(); }
554 )cc";
555 auto MatchesCall = cxxMemberCallExpr(on(callExpr()));
556 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(Snippet3, MatchesCall));
557}

559TEST(MatcherCXXMemberCallExpr, OnImplicitObjectArgument) {
560 auto Snippet1 = R"cc(
561 struct Y {
562 void m();
563 };
564 void z(Y y) { y.m(); }
565 )cc";
566 auto Snippet2 = R"cc(
567 struct Y {
568 void m();
569 };
570 struct X : public Y {};
571 void z(X x) { x.m(); }
572 )cc";
573 auto MatchesY = cxxMemberCallExpr(
574 onImplicitObjectArgument(hasType(cxxRecordDecl(hasName("Y")))));
575 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(Snippet1, MatchesY));
576 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(Snippet2, MatchesY));
577
578 auto MatchesX = cxxMemberCallExpr(
579 onImplicitObjectArgument(hasType(cxxRecordDecl(hasName("X")))));
580 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(Snippet2, MatchesX));
581
582 // Parens are not ignored.
583 auto Snippet3 = R"cc(
584 struct Y {
585 void m();
586 };
587 Y g();
588 void z(Y y) { (g()).m(); }
589 )cc";
590 auto MatchesCall = cxxMemberCallExpr(onImplicitObjectArgument(callExpr()));
591 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(Snippet3, MatchesCall));
592}

618TEST(ForEachArgumentWithParam, ReportsNoFalsePositives) {
619 StatementMatcher ArgumentY =
620 declRefExpr(to(varDecl(hasName("y")))).bind("arg");
621 DeclarationMatcher IntParam = parmVarDecl(hasType(isInteger())).bind("param");
622 StatementMatcher CallExpr =
623 callExpr(forEachArgumentWithParam(ArgumentY, IntParam));
624
625 // IntParam does not match.
626 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("void f(int* i) { int* y; f(y); }", CallExpr));
627 // ArgumentY does not match.

1130TEST(Matcher, BinaryOperatorTypes) {
1131 // Integration test that verifies the AST provides all binary operators in
1132 // a way we expect.
1133 // FIXME: Operator ','
1134 EXPECT_TRUE(
1135 matches("void x() { 3, 4; }", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName(","))));
1136 EXPECT_TRUE(
1137 matches("bool b; bool c = (b = true);",
1138 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("="))));
1139 EXPECT_TRUE(
1140 matches("bool b = 1 != 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("!="))));
1141 EXPECT_TRUE(
1142 matches("bool b = 1 == 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("=="))));
1143 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("bool b = 1 < 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("<"))));
1144 EXPECT_TRUE(
1145 matches("bool b = 1 <= 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("<="))));
1146 EXPECT_TRUE(
1147 matches("int i = 1 << 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("<<"))));
1148 EXPECT_TRUE(
1149 matches("int i = 1; int j = (i <<= 2);",
1150 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("<<="))));
1151 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("bool b = 1 > 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName(">"))));
1152 EXPECT_TRUE(
1153 matches("bool b = 1 >= 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName(">="))));
1154 EXPECT_TRUE(
1155 matches("int i = 1 >> 2;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName(">>"))));
1156 EXPECT_TRUE(
1157 matches("int i = 1; int j = (i >>= 2);",
1158 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName(">>="))));
1159 EXPECT_TRUE(
1160 matches("int i = 42 ^ 23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("^"))));
1161 EXPECT_TRUE(
1162 matches("int i = 42; int j = (i ^= 42);",
1163 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("^="))));
1164 EXPECT_TRUE(
1165 matches("int i = 42 % 23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("%"))));
1166 EXPECT_TRUE(
1167 matches("int i = 42; int j = (i %= 42);",
1168 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("%="))));
1169 EXPECT_TRUE(
1170 matches("bool b = 42 &23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("&"))));
1171 EXPECT_TRUE(
1172 matches("bool b = true && false;",
1173 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("&&"))));
1174 EXPECT_TRUE(
1175 matches("bool b = true; bool c = (b &= false);",
1176 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("&="))));
1177 EXPECT_TRUE(
1178 matches("bool b = 42 | 23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("|"))));
1179 EXPECT_TRUE(
1180 matches("bool b = true || false;",
1181 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("||"))));
1182 EXPECT_TRUE(
1183 matches("bool b = true; bool c = (b |= false);",
1184 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("|="))));
1185 EXPECT_TRUE(
1186 matches("int i = 42 *23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("*"))));
1187 EXPECT_TRUE(
1188 matches("int i = 42; int j = (i *= 23);",
1189 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("*="))));
1190 EXPECT_TRUE(
1191 matches("int i = 42 / 23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("/"))));
1192 EXPECT_TRUE(
1193 matches("int i = 42; int j = (i /= 23);",
1194 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("/="))));
1195 EXPECT_TRUE(
1196 matches("int i = 42 + 23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("+"))));
1197 EXPECT_TRUE(
1198 matches("int i = 42; int j = (i += 23);",
1199 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("+="))));
1200 EXPECT_TRUE(
1201 matches("int i = 42 - 23;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("-"))));
1202 EXPECT_TRUE(
1203 matches("int i = 42; int j = (i -= 23);",
1204 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("-="))));
1205 EXPECT_TRUE(
1206 matches("struct A { void x() { void (A::*a)(); (this->*a)(); } };",
1207 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("->*"))));
1208 EXPECT_TRUE(
1209 matches("struct A { void x() { void (A::*a)(); ((*this).*a)(); } };",
1210 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName(".*"))));
1211
1212 // Member expressions as operators are not supported in matches.
1213 EXPECT_TRUE(
1214 notMatches("struct A { void x(A *a) { a->x(this); } };",
1215 binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("->"))));
1216
1217 // Initializer assignments are not represented as operator equals.
1218 EXPECT_TRUE(
1219 notMatches("bool b = true;", binaryOperator(hasOperatorName("="))));
1220
1221 // Array indexing is not represented as operator.
1222 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("int a[42]; void x() { a[23]; }", unaryOperator()));
1223
1224 // Overloaded operators do not match at all.
1225 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(
1226 "struct A { bool operator&&(const A &a) const { return false; } };"
1227 "void x() { A a, b; a && b; }",
1228 binaryOperator()));
1229}

1246TEST(Matcher, UnaryOperatorTypes) {
1247 // Integration test that verifies the AST provides all unary operators in
1248 // a way we expect.
1249 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("bool b = !true;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("!"))));
1250 EXPECT_TRUE(
1251 matches("bool b; bool *p = &b;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("&"))));
1252 EXPECT_TRUE(matches("int i = ~ 1;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("~"))));
1253 EXPECT_TRUE(
1254 matches("bool *p; bool b = *p;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("*"))));
1255 EXPECT_TRUE(
1256 matches("int i; int j = +i;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("+"))));
1257 EXPECT_TRUE(
1258 matches("int i; int j = -i;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("-"))));
1259 EXPECT_TRUE(
1260 matches("int i; int j = ++i;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("++"))));
1261 EXPECT_TRUE(
1262 matches("int i; int j = i++;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("++"))));
1263 EXPECT_TRUE(
1264 matches("int i; int j = --i;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("--"))));
1265 EXPECT_TRUE(
1266 matches("int i; int j = i--;", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("--"))));
1267
1268 // We don't match conversion operators.
1269 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("int i; double d = (double)i;", unaryOperator()));
1270
1271 // Function calls are not represented as operator.
1272 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches("void f(); void x() { f(); }", unaryOperator()));
1273
1274 // Overloaded operators do not match at all.
1275 // FIXME: We probably want to add that.
1276 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(
1277 "struct A { bool operator!() const { return false; } };"
1278 "void x() { A a; !a; }", unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("!"))));

1835TEST(LoopingMatchers, DoNotOverwritePreviousMatchResultOnFailure) {
1836 // Those matchers cover all the cases where an inner matcher is called
1837 // and there is not a 1:1 relationship between the match of the outer
1838 // matcher and the match of the inner matcher.
1839 // The pattern to look for is:
1840 // ... return InnerMatcher.matches(...); ...
1841 // In which case no special handling is needed.
1842 //
1843 // On the other hand, if there are multiple alternative matches
1844 // (for example forEach*) or matches might be discarded (for example has*)
1845 // the implementation must make sure that the discarded matches do not
1846 // affect the bindings.
1847 // When new such matchers are added, add a test here that:
1848 // - matches a simple node, and binds it as the first thing in the matcher:
1849 // recordDecl(decl().bind("x"), hasName("X")))
1850 // - uses the matcher under test afterwards in a way that not the first
1851 // alternative is matched; for anyOf, that means the first branch
1852 // would need to return false; for hasAncestor, it means that not
1853 // the direct parent matches the inner matcher.
1854
1855 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1856 "class X { int y; };",
1857 recordDecl(
1858 recordDecl().bind("x"), hasName("::X"),
1859 anyOf(forEachDescendant(recordDecl(hasName("Y"))), anything())),
1860 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXRecordDecl>>("x", 1)));
1861 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1862 "class X {};", recordDecl(recordDecl().bind("x"), hasName("::X"),
1863 anyOf(unless(anything()), anything())),
1864 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXRecordDecl>>("x", 1)));
1865 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1866 "template<typename T1, typename T2> class X {}; X<float, int> x;",
1867 classTemplateSpecializationDecl(
1868 decl().bind("x"),
1869 hasAnyTemplateArgument(refersToType(asString("int")))),
1870 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1871 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1872 "class X { void f(); void g(); };",
1873 cxxRecordDecl(decl().bind("x"), hasMethod(hasName("g"))),
1874 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1875 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1876 "class X { X() : a(1), b(2) {} double a; int b; };",
1877 recordDecl(decl().bind("x"),
1878 has(cxxConstructorDecl(
1879 hasAnyConstructorInitializer(forField(hasName("b")))))),
1880 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1881 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1882 "void x(int, int) { x(0, 42); }",
1883 callExpr(expr().bind("x"), hasAnyArgument(integerLiteral(equals(42)))),
1884 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Expr>>("x", 1)));
1885 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1886 "void x(int, int y) {}",
1887 functionDecl(decl().bind("x"), hasAnyParameter(hasName("y"))),
1888 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1889 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1890 "void x() { return; if (true) {} }",
1891 functionDecl(decl().bind("x"),
1892 has(compoundStmt(hasAnySubstatement(ifStmt())))),
1893 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1894 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1895 "namespace X { void b(int); void b(); }"
1896 "using X::b;",
1897 usingDecl(decl().bind("x"), hasAnyUsingShadowDecl(hasTargetDecl(
1898 functionDecl(parameterCountIs(1))))),
1899 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1900 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1901 "class A{}; class B{}; class C : B, A {};",
1902 cxxRecordDecl(decl().bind("x"), isDerivedFrom("::A")),
1903 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1904 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1905 "class A{}; typedef A B; typedef A C; typedef A D;"
1906 "class E : A {};",
1907 cxxRecordDecl(decl().bind("x"), isDerivedFrom("C")),
1908 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1909 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1910 "class A { class B { void f() {} }; };",
1911 functionDecl(decl().bind("x"), hasAncestor(recordDecl(hasName("::A")))),
1912 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1913 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1914 "template <typename T> struct A { struct B {"
1915 " void f() { if(true) {} }"
1916 "}; };"
1917 "void t() { A<int>::B b; b.f(); }",
1918 ifStmt(stmt().bind("x"), hasAncestor(recordDecl(hasName("::A")))),
1919 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Stmt>>("x", 2)));
1920 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1921 "class A {};",
1922 recordDecl(hasName("::A"), decl().bind("x"), unless(hasName("fooble"))),
1923 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1924 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
1925 "class A { A() : s(), i(42) {} const char *s; int i; };",
1926 cxxConstructorDecl(hasName("::A::A"), decl().bind("x"),
1927 forEachConstructorInitializer(forField(hasName("i")))),
1928 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<Decl>>("x", 1)));
1929}

2150TEST(HasParent, NoDuplicateParents) {
2151 class HasDuplicateParents : public BoundNodesCallback {
2152 public:
2153 bool run(const BoundNodes *Nodes) override { return false; }
2154 bool run(const BoundNodes *Nodes, ASTContext *Context) override {
2155 const Stmt *Node = Nodes->getNodeAs<Stmt>("node");
2156 std::set<const void *> Parents;
2157 for (const auto &Parent : Context->getParents(*Node)) {
2158 if (!Parents.insert(Parent.getMemoizationData()).second) {
2159 return true;
2160 }
2161 }
2162 return false;
2163 }
2164 };
2165 EXPECT_FALSE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
2166 "template <typename T> int Foo() { return 1 + 2; }\n"
2167 "int x = Foo<int>() + Foo<unsigned>();",
2168 stmt().bind("node"), llvm::make_unique<HasDuplicateParents>()));
2169}

2325 // Nested names: a, a::A and a::A::B.
2326 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<NestedNameSpecifierLoc>>("x", 3)));
2327}
2328template <typename T> class VerifyMatchOnNode : public BoundNodesCallback {
2329public:
2330 VerifyMatchOnNode(StringRef Id, const internal::Matcher<T> &InnerMatcher,
2331 StringRef InnerId)
2332 : Id(Id), InnerMatcher(InnerMatcher), InnerId(InnerId) {
2333 }
2334
2335 bool run(const BoundNodes *Nodes) override { return false; }
2336
2337 bool run(const BoundNodes *Nodes, ASTContext *Context) override {
2338 const T *Node = Nodes->getNodeAs<T>(Id);
2339 return selectFirst<T>(InnerId, match(InnerMatcher, *Node, *Context)) !=
2340 nullptr;
2341 }
2342private:
2343 std::string Id;
2344 internal::Matcher<T> InnerMatcher;
2345 std::string InnerId;
2346};

2390TEST(StatementMatcher, ForFunction) {
2391 const auto CppString1 =
2392 "struct PosVec {"
2393 " PosVec& operator=(const PosVec&) {"
2394 " auto x = [] { return 1; };"
2395 " return *this;"
2396 " }"
2397 "};";
2398 const auto CppString2 =
2399 "void F() {"
2400 " struct S {"
2401 " void F2() {"
2402 " return;"
2403 " }"
2404 " };"
2405 "}";
2406 EXPECT_TRUE(
2407 matches(
2408 CppString1,
2409 returnStmt(forFunction(hasName("operator=")),
2410 has(unaryOperator(hasOperatorName("*"))))));
2411 EXPECT_TRUE(
2412 notMatches(
2413 CppString1,
2414 returnStmt(forFunction(hasName("operator=")),
2415 has(integerLiteral()))));
2416 EXPECT_TRUE(
2417 matches(
2418 CppString1,
2419 returnStmt(forFunction(hasName("operator()")),
2420 has(integerLiteral()))));
2421 EXPECT_TRUE(matches(CppString2, returnStmt(forFunction(hasName("F2")))));
2422 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(CppString2, returnStmt(forFunction(hasName("F")))));
2423}

2425TEST(Matcher, ForEachOverriden) {
2426 const auto ForEachOverriddenInClass = [](const char *ClassName) {
2427 return cxxMethodDecl(ofClass(hasName(ClassName)), isVirtual(),
2428 forEachOverridden(cxxMethodDecl().bind("overridden")))
2429 .bind("override");
2430 };
2431 static const char Code1[] = "class A { virtual void f(); };"
2432 "class B : public A { void f(); };"
2433 "class C : public B { void f(); };";
2434 // C::f overrides A::f.
2435 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
2436 Code1, ForEachOverriddenInClass("C"),
2437 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXMethodDecl>>("override", "f", 1)));
2438 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
2439 Code1, ForEachOverriddenInClass("C"),
2440 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXMethodDecl>>("overridden", "f",
2441 1)));
2442 // B::f overrides A::f.
2443 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
2444 Code1, ForEachOverriddenInClass("B"),
2445 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXMethodDecl>>("override", "f", 1)));
2446 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
2447 Code1, ForEachOverriddenInClass("B"),
2448 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXMethodDecl>>("overridden", "f",
2449 1)));
2450 // A::f overrides nothing.
2451 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(Code1, ForEachOverriddenInClass("A")));
2452
2453 static const char Code2[] =
2454 "class A1 { virtual void f(); };"
2455 "class A2 { virtual void f(); };"
2456 "class B : public A1, public A2 { void f(); };";
2457 // B::f overrides A1::f and A2::f. This produces two matches.
2458 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
2459 Code2, ForEachOverriddenInClass("B"),
2460 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXMethodDecl>>("override", "f", 2)));
2461 EXPECT_TRUE(matchAndVerifyResultTrue(
2462 Code2, ForEachOverriddenInClass("B"),
2463 llvm::make_unique<VerifyIdIsBoundTo<CXXMethodDecl>>("overridden", "f",
2464 2)));
2465 // A1::f overrides nothing.
2466 EXPECT_TRUE(notMatches(Code2, ForEachOverriddenInClass("A1")));
2467}
